articles.author: SARAH EL DEEB
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — Insurgents breached Syria’s largest city Friday and clashed with government forces for the first time since 2016, according to a war monitor and fighters, in a surprise attack that sent residents fleeing and added fresh uncertainty to a region reeling from multiple wars.
articles.title: In a shock offensive, insurgents breach Syria's largest city for the first time since 2016

articles.author: KAREEM CHEHAYEB
articles.description: BEIRUT (AP) — Hours after a U.S.-brokered ceasefire to end the war between Israel and Hezbollah went into effect, Lebanon woke up to the sound of celebratory gunfire instead of Israeli airstrikes and drones buzzing overhead.
articles.title: Battered by war and divisions, Lebanon faces a long list of challenges after ceasefire deal

articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.description: Two children and a woman were crushed to death Friday as a crowd of Palestinians pushed to get bread at a bakery in the Gaza Strip amid a worsening food crisis in the war-ravaged territory, medical officials said.
articles.title: Middle East latest: 2 children and a woman crushed to death outside Gaza bakery amid food shortage

articles.author: MATTHEW DALY
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — President-elect Donald Trump is set to create a National Energy Council that he says will establish American “energy dominance” around the world as he seeks to boost U.S.
articles.title: Donald Trump's call for 'energy dominance' is likely to run into real-world limits

articles.author: ANNE D'INNOCENZIO, HALELUYA HADERO and ALEXANDRA OLSON
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Retailers used giveaways and big discounts to reward U.S. shoppers who ventured out for Black Friday even as earlier offers, the prospect of better bargains in the days ahead and the ease of e-commerce drained much of the excitement from the holiday shopping season's much-hyped kickoff.
articles.title: Retailers coax Black Friday shoppers into stores with big discounts and giveaways

articles.author: SAMYA KULLAB and VOLODYMYR YURCHUK
articles.description: KYIV, Ukraine (AP) — Desertion is starving the Ukrainian army of desperately needed manpower and crippling its battle plans at a crucial time in its war with Russia, which could put Kyiv at a clear disadvantage in future ceasefire talks.
articles.title: Desertion threatens to starve Ukraine's forces at a crucial time in its war with Russia

articles.author: CHINEDU ASADU
articles.description: ABUJA, Nigeria (AP) — At least 27 people died and more than 100, mostly women, were missing on Friday, after a boat transporting them to a food market capsized along the River Niger in northern Nigeria, authorities said.
articles.title: Nigeria confirms that at least 27 people died and more than 100 are missing after boat capsized

articles.author: BRIAN MELLEY
articles.description: LONDON (AP) — British lawmakers are expected to vote Friday on a law proposed to help terminally ill adults end their lives.
articles.title: Bill to legalize assisted dying in England and Wales faces heated parliamentary debate

articles.author: THOMAS ADAMSON and JOHN LEICESTER
articles.description: PARIS (AP) — After more than five years of frenetic, but sometimes interrupted, reconstruction work, Notre Dame Cathedral showed itself anew to the world Friday, with rebuilt soaring ceilings and creamy good-as-new stonework erasing somber memories of its devastating fire in 2019.
articles.title: Notre Dame Cathedral unveils its new interior 5 years after devastating fire

articles.author: TRAVIS LOLLER
articles.description: ON BOARD THE SANTA TRAIN (AP) — Since 1943, the people of Appalachian Kentucky, Virginia, and Tennessee have looked forward to Santa's arrival. Not in a sleigh on their rooftops, but on a train. The Santa Train marks its 82nd running this year, bringing presents and joy to small towns along a 110-mile portion of the CSX rail line tucked into remote coal-country river valleys.
articles.title: Santa's annual train visit delivers hope and magic to one corner of coal country
